'''Saša Kalajdžić''' ({{lang-sr-Cyrl|Саша Калајџић}}; born 7 July 1997) is an Austrian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Striker (association football)|striker]] for [[Austrian Football Bundesliga|Austrian Bundesliga]] club [[LASK]] on loan from {{English football updater|WolverhW}} club [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] and the [[Austria national football team|Austria national team]].

Kalajdžić began his senior career playing in the third and fourth tiers of Austrian football with SR Donaufeld Wien. In 2016, he signed for [[Austrian Football Bundesliga|Austrian Bundesliga]] club [[FC Admira Wacker Mödling|Admira Wacker]], where he scored twelve goals in 35 matches for the first team. He joined German club [[VfB Stuttgart]] in July 2019, sustaining a serious knee injury shortly after joining and not making his debut until May 2020. Nevertheless, he would go on to score 24 goals in 60 matches for the club. In August 2022, Kalajdžić was signed by English club Wolverhampton Wanderers for a reported fee of £15&nbsp;million.

Kalajdžić played for Austria at [[Austria national under-21 football team|under-21 level]], before making his senior international debut in October 2020. He was part of Austria's squad at [[UEFA Euro 2020|Euro 2020]].

==Club career==

===FC Admira Wacker Mödling===
[[File:20170628 ADM vs Gyirmot FC 0539 (cropped).jpg|thumb|Kalajdžić with [[FC Admira Wacker Mödling|Admira Wacker]] in 2017]]
Born in the Austrian capital [[Vienna]], Kalajdžić joined [[FC Admira Wacker Mödling]] in 2016, from SR Donaufeld Wien.<ref name="earlycareer">{{cite web|url=https://kurier.at/sport/fussball/rapid-stuermersuche-admiras-kalajdzic-soll-es-richten/400391084|title=Rapid-Stürmersuche: Admiras Kalajdzic soll es richten|website=kurier.at|language=de|date=29 January 2019|access-date=17 December 2020}}</ref> He originally played as a midfielder for the club's reserve side in the [[Austrian Regionalliga East]], before being converted into a forward.<ref name="earlycareer"/>

===VfB Stuttgart===
On 5 July 2019, Kalajdžić signed a four-year contract with the German club [[VfB Stuttgart]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vfb.de/en/vfb/latest/news/professionals/2019/verpflichtung-sasa-kalajdzic/|title=VfB sign Sasa Kalajdzic|work=vfb.de|publisher=[[VfB Stuttgart]]|date=5 July 2019|accessdate=5 July 2019}}</ref> Shortly after his arrival, he suffered a torn [[cruciate ligament]] during a preseason training camp.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kicker.de/stuttgart-gegen-hsv-2020-bundesliga-4589189/analyse|title=3:2 nach 0:2! VfB kommt zurück und schlägt den HSV|website=kicker}}</ref> He made his league debut on 28 May 2020, coming on as a substitute in the 78th minute of matchday 28 of the [[2019–20 2. Bundesliga|2019–20]] [[2. Bundesliga]] season against [[Hamburger SV]], and scored his first goal on matchday 33 during a 6–0 rout of [[FC Nuremberg]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kicker.de/nuernberg-gegen-stuttgart-2020-bundesliga-4589234/analyse|title=Doppelpacker Gonzalez und Karazor: Stuttgart fertigt Nürnberg ab|website=kicker}}</ref>

In the [[2020-21 Bundesliga|following season]], Kalajdžić frequently led the line for VfB Stuttgart, finishing the season as the 6th top scorer in the [[Bundesliga]] with 16 goals,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/top-scorer-2020-21-lewandowski-haaland-sancho-gnabry-thuram-hwang-12909|title=Robert Lewandowski, Erling Haaland, Andrej Kramaric and the race to become the Bundesliga's top scorer|website=bundesliga.com}}</ref> helping his team finish 9th. The next season, he scored the winner in Stuttgart's 3&ndash;2 win over [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]] on matchday 25,<ref name="Stuttgart 3-2 Gladbach">{{cite web |title=Der coole Kalajdzic krönt eine famose VfB-Aufholjagd |url=https://www.kicker.de/stuttgart-gegen-mgladbach-2022-bundesliga-4721714/analyse |website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]] |access-date=6 March 2022}}</ref> and the team's first goal in a 2–1 win over [[1. FC Köln]] on the final matchday, to ensure the club's presence in the Bundesliga for the 2022–23 season.<ref name="Wataru Endo's injury-time winner over Cologne seals dramatic salvation for VfB Stuttgart">{{cite web |title=Wataru Endo's injury-time winner over Cologne seals dramatic salvation for VfB Stuttgart |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/stuttgart-cologne-live-team-news-match-stats-modeste-marmoush-sosa-kalajdzic-19904|publisher=bundesliga.com |access-date=17 May 2022}}</ref>

===Wolverhampton Wanderers===
On 31 August 2022, English club [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] announced that they had signed Kalajdžić on a five-year deal, with the option to extend for a further 12 months.<ref>{{cite news |title=Kalajdzic completes Wolves move |url=https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/mens-first-team/20220831-kalajdzic-completes-wolves-move/ |access-date=31 August 2022 |publisher=Wolverhampton Wanderers FC |date=31 August 2022}}</ref> The fee was undisclosed by the club, but was reported to be £15&nbsp;million.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62737468|title=Wolves complete signing of Sasa Kalajdzic from Stuttgart for £15m|website=[[BBC Sport]]|date=31 August 2022}}</ref> He made his debut three days later as a starter in a 1–0 [[Premier League]] win against [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] at [[Molineux Stadium|Molineux]], but was substituted at half-time due to injury which was later confirmed as an [[Anterior Cruciate Ligament|ACL]] tear requiring surgery.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62697701|title=Wolverhampton Wanderers 1–0 Southampton: Daniel Podence earns hosts first league win of season|first=Matthew|last=Howarth|website=BBC Sport|date=3 September 2022}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.molineux.news/news/wolves-striker-sasa-kalajdzic-to-undergo-surgery-for-torn-acl/|title=Wolves striker Sasa Kalajdzic to undergo surgery for torn ACL|first=Tom|last=Procter|website=Molineux News|date=5 September 2022}}</ref> Wolves subsequently announced that the player underwent reparative surgery on 6 September, and cautioned that the typical rehabilitation period after such a procedure is nine months.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/mens-first-team/20220916-injury-update-kalajdzic-jimenez-and-chiquinho/|title=Injury update: Kalajdzic, Jimenez and Chiquinho|website=wolves.co.uk|date=16 September 2022|access-date=17 September 2022}}</ref>

Kalajdžić made his second appearance for Wolves (and first since 3 September 2022) against [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] on 14 August 2023 as a late substitute. Kalajdžić again entered the field as a late substitute against [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] on 26 August 2023, and proceeded to score his first goal for Wolves in the 87th minute to help them win 1–0 away at [[Goodison Park]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66552609|title=Everton 0–1 Wolves: Sasa Kalajdzic scores late winner for visitors|first= Shamoon|last=Hafez|website=BBC Sport|date=26 August 2023|access-date=29 August 2023}}</ref>

Kalajdžić scored his second goal for Wolves in his next match – his first start for the club since 3 September 2022 – a home game in the [[EFL Cup]] against [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]] on 29 August 2023 that Wolves won 5–0.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66577642|title=Wolverhampton Wanderers 5–0 Blackpool: Matt Doherty scores twice as hosts progress|work=BBC Sport |date=29 August 2023 }}</ref>

Kalajdžić scored his second Premier League goal, again as a substitute, in a 2–1 Wolves win away to [[AFC Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] on 21 October 2023.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/oct/21/bournemouth-wolves-premier-league-match-report|title=Kalajdzic completes Wolves comeback win at 10-man Bournemouth|work=[[The Observer]]|first=Simon|last=Mail|date=21 October 2023|access-date=22 October 2023}}</ref> It was the second time in the season he had scored a late winning goal for Wolves in a Premier League fixture to secure an away win.

==== Loan to Eintracht Frankfurt ====
On 7 January 2024, Wolves sent Kalajdžić on loan to Bundesliga club [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] until the end of the [[2023–24 Eintracht Frankfurt season|2023–24 season]].<ref>{{cite web |date=7 January 2024 |title=Eintracht verpflichtet Sasa Kalajdzic |trans-title=Eintracht signs Sasa Kalajdzic |url=https://profis.eintracht.de/news/eintracht-verpflichtet-sasa-kalajdzic-155911 |publisher=Eintracht Frankfurt |language=de}}</ref> On 15 February, he scored his first goal for the club in a 2–2 away draw against [[Royale Union Saint-Gilloise|Union Saint-Gilloise]] during the [[2023–24 UEFA Europa Conference League|Conference League]] knockout round play-offs.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68308747 |title=Union Saint-Gilloise 2–2 Eintracht Frankfurt |work=BBC Sport |date=15 February 2024 }}</ref> On 18 February, Kalajdžić suffered a third ACL tear in the space of five years in a Bundesliga match against [[SC Freiburg]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://profis.eintracht.de/news/diagnose-sasa-kalajdzic-156922 |title=Diagnose Sasa Kalajdzic |publisher=Eintracht Frankfurt |date= 18 February 2024 | access-date = 19 February 2024}}</ref>

==== Return to Wolverhampton ====
Kalajdžić missed the entire 2024–25 season due to his ACL injury.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/mens-first-team/20250612-summer-special-sasa-kalajdzic/ |title=Summer Special {{!}} Sasa Kalajdzic |publisher=Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C. |date=12 June 2025 }}</ref>

==== Loan to LASK ====
On 5 September 2025, Wolves loaned out Kalajdžić a second time, this time to Austrian side [[LASK]].<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/loan-watch/20250905-kalajdzic-returns-to-austria-on-loan/ |title = Kalajdzic returns to Austria on loan |publisher = Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C. |date=5 September 2025 }}</ref> On 30 January 2026, he scored his first goal for the club in a 3–2 victory over [[FC Blau-Weiß Linz|Blau-Weiß Linz]] in the [[2025–26 Austrian Cup|Austrian Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lask.at/de/m/matches/pros/uniqa-oefb-cup/viertelfinale-uniqa-oefb-cup |title="Die Dramaturgie war unglaublich" |publisher=LASK |language=de |date=2 February 2026 }}</ref> Later that year, on 26 April, he netted a brace, including a goal from his own half, and provided an assist in a 5–1 away victory over [[TSV Hartberg]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/sasa-kalajdzic-scores-from-halfway-line-as-on-loan-wolves-striker-hits-purple-patch-42777346 |title=Sasa Kalajdzic scores from halfway line as on-loan Wolves striker hits purple patch |publisher=OneFootball |date=27 April 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
Kalajdžić made six appearances for Austria at [[Austria national under-21 football team|under-21]] level.<ref name="donaufeldstats">{{cite web|url=https://www.besoccer.com/player/s-kalajdzic-346363|title=S. Kalajdžić|website=BeSoccer|access-date=12 August 2022}}</ref> He made his senior international debut for [[Austria national football team|Austria]] on 14 October 2020, in a [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League B|Nations League]] 1–0 victory against [[Romania national football team|Romania]], as an extra time substitute for [[Michael Gregoritsch]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Einzelkritik zu Rumänien gegen Österreich|url=https://www.laola1.at/de/red/fussball/oefb-nationalteam/a-team/spiele/noten--die-laola1-einzelkritik-zu-rumaenien-gegen-oesterreich/|website=[[Laola1]]|date=14 October 2020|language=de}}</ref>

On 25 March 2021, he scored his first two international goals in a 2–2 away draw with [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] during [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|2022 FIFA World Cup qualification]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Scotland 2–2 Austria|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56438742|website=BBC Sport|date=25 March 2021}}</ref> He was included in the squad for [[UEFA Euro 2020|Euro 2020]], where he scored a goal in a 2–1 loss after extra-time against [[Italy national football team|Italy]] in the round of 16.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Sasa Kalajdzic scores as Austria suffer late defeat against Italy|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4210417/2021/06/07/sasa-kalajdzic-scores-as-austria-suffer-late-defeat-against-italy/|website=The Athletic|date=27 June 2021}}</ref>

==Style of play==
[[File:FC Red Bull Salzburg gegen Admira Wacker Mödling (3. Februar 2018) 45.jpg|thumb|Kalajdžić jumping for a header in 2018]]
Due to his two-metre stature and relatively slender build, Kalajdžić received comparisons with the English striker [[Peter Crouch]], who similarly to him functioned as an out-and-out [[target man]]. During his youth career, Kalajdžić also played as a [[holding midfielder]] and referred to [[Nemanja Matić]] as an inspiration.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/stuttgart-striker-sasa-kalajdzic-come-and-get-me-plea/3c6g17tw7gj1aq0dht9nqv2q|title=Stuttgart striker Sasa Kalajdzic issues come-and-get-me plea to Liverpool|website=Goal (website)}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/sasa-kalajdzic-who-is-the-wolves-austria-striker-peter-crouch-eintracht-frankfurt-16174|title=Sasa Kalajdzic: Who is the VfB Stuttgart and Austria striker?|website=bundesliga.com}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Born in Austria, Kalajdžić is of [[Serbs|Serbian]] descent.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://srbin.info/sport/srpski-dzin-u-dresu-austrije-sasa-kalajdzic-na-meti-kelna-stutgarta-lidsa/?lang=lat|title=SRPSKI DŽIN U DRESU AUSTRIJE – Saša Kalajdžić na meti Kelna, Štutgarta, Lidsa|website=srbin.info|date=17 June 2019 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/sasa-kalajdzic-interview-on-peter-crouch-comparison-vfb-stuttgart-striker-13397|title=VfB Stuttgart striker Sasa Kalajdzic on Peter Crouch comparisons and living the dream in the Bundesliga|website=bundesliga.com – the official Bundesliga website}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Hagenauer |first1=Andreas |title=Saša Kalajdžić: Golgeter |url=https://telesport.telegram.hr/price/sasa-kalajdzic-golgeter/ |website=Telesport |access-date=4 September 2021 |language=hr |date=18 May 2021}}</ref>

